label.value: antibiotic sensitive beta-prime subunit of RNA polymerase (rpoA)

definition.value: RNA polymerase is a multisubunit enzyme that is necessary for transcription. Catalyzes the transcription of DNA into RNA using the four ribonucleoside triphosphates as substrates.
RNA polymerase is a multisubunit enzyme that is necessary for transcription. Mutations in rpoA gene confer antibiotic resistance.
rpoA catalyzes the transcription of DNA into RNA and mutations confer resistance to rifampicin.

label.value: Mycobacterium tuberculosis rpoA mutations confer resistance to rifampicin

value.value: Mutations in rpoA that contribute to or confer resistance to rifampicin antibiotic.

definition.value: Point mutations in DNA gyrase subunit B (gyrB) of Neisseria gonorrhoeae can result in resistance to Zoliflodacin.

label.value: 50S rRNA with mutation conferring resistance to macrolide antibiotics

definition.value: Nucleotide point mutations in the 50S rRNA subunit (not in the 23s rRNA range) may confer resistance to macrolide antibiotics.

Genes ppsA-E constitute an operon encoding enzymes involved in the biosynthesis of phthiocerol dimycocerosate and other lipids in Mycobacterium tuberculosis. Mutations within this region can result in resistance to pyrazinamide.

label.value: 50S rRNA with mutation conferring antibiotic resistance

definition.value: Mutations in the prokaryotic 50S ribosomal RNA subunit which disrupt binding sites and thereby reduce antibiotic efficacy.

label.value: Neisseria gonorrhoeae mtrC with mutation conferring resistance to azithromycin

value.value: Mutation in the mtrC efflux pump of Neisseria gonorrhoea shown to confer resistance to azithromycin, a macrolide type antibiotic.
Known antibiotic-resistant variants of emb arabinosyltransferases, primarily in Mycobacterium and conferring resistance to ethambutol through point mutation.
A tetracycline efflux MFS Transporter from Providencia sp. Y14.
QnrVC2 is a class 1 integron found in Ciprofloxacin-resistant Vibro choleraeO1.
TxR is a putative transcription regulator that plays a role in conferring tetracycline resistance. It is required for proper functioning of Tet35.
QacE is a resistance gene conferring resistance to antiseptics.
QacEdelta1 is a resistance gene conferring resistance to antiseptics. It is different from QacE only at the 3'-terminus.
IDC beta-lactamases are class C beta-lactamases inc. cephalosporinases and carbapenemases.
IDC-2 is an IDC beta-lactamase and an integron cephalosprinase.
IDC-2 is an IDC beta-lactamase and an integron cephalosprinase.
Vibro metallo-B-lactamase, also known as VMB is a carbapenemase beta-lactamase gene family.
Vibrio metallo-B-lactamase 1, also known as VMB-1, is carbapenemase beta-lactamase that is found in plasmid pVB1796 from Vibrio alginolyticus.
CMY-150 is a CMY-2 variant differing by 15 amino-acid substitutions. It confers higher resistance levels to ceftazidime and aztreonam compared to CMY-2.
LMB is an AMR Gene family belonging to subclass B3 metallo-beta-lactamases.
LMB-1 is a subclass B3 metallo-beta-lactamase that confers resistance to penams, cephalosporins, and carbapenems.
IMP-68 is a subclass B1 metallo-beta-lactamase that confers resistance to carbapenems.
The cfr(D) group are cfr(D) genes found in Enterococcus faecium that confer resistance to vancomycin, teicoplanin and linezolid.
cfr(D) is found in Enterococcus faecium. It confers resistance to vancomycin, teicoplanin, and linezolid.
cfr(E) is a cfr-like gene described by (Stojkovic et al, 2019). It is found on transposon Tn6218 and found in Clostridioides difficile.
The gene cfr(E) is a cfr-like gene found in Clostridioides difficile isolate DF11. It confers resistance to antibiotics targeting to the 23s rRNA through hypermethylation of nucleotide A2503.
FosL1 is related to FosA-like genes. It is a plasmid-encoded fosfomycin resistant gene found in E. coli.

definition.value: Antibiotic adjuvants shown to inhibit the action of ATP synthase, restoring antibiotic activity by depolarizing the bacterial membrane.

value.value: Venturicidin A is an ATP synthase inhibitor and antibiotic adjuvant produced in actinomycetes. In the presence of aminoglycoside antibiotics such as gentamicin, Venturicidin A showed to restore susceptibility to aminoglycosides in resistant bacteria.
FRI-4 is a carbapenem-hydrolyzing Class A beta-lactamase gene found in Enterobacter asburiae.

definition.value: FRI-5 is a carbapenem-hydrolyzing Class A beta-lactamase gene found in Enterobacter cloacae.

value.value: FRI-6 is a carbapenem-hydrolyzing Class A beta-lactamase gene found in Enterobacter cloacae.

definition.value: FRI-7 is a carbapenem-hydrolyzing Class A beta-lactamase gene found in Enterobacter asburiae.
FRI-8 is a carbapenem-hydrolyzing Class A beta-lactamase gene found in Enterobacter sp. 18A13. It is from a plasmid.
FRI-9 is a carbapenem-hydrolyzing Class A beta-lactamase gene found in Enterobacter asburiae.
FLC-1 is part of the FRI beta-lactamase family. It is a class A carbapenem-hydrolyzing beta-lactamase from Enterobacter cloacae.

value.value: YRC is a ambler class C beta-lactamase from Yersinia ruckeri. It confers resistance penams and cephalosporins.
Yrc-1 is a ampC-like beta-lactamase that confers resistance to penams and cephalosporins. It is an ambler class C beta-lactamase.

BLMT is a bleomycin (Bm) resistance protein, encoded by the ble gene on the transposon Tn5. This protein confers a survival advantage to Escherichia coli host cells. BLMT confers resistance to bleomycin.

definition.value: ADC-159 is an ADC beta-lactamase and a ambler class C beta-lactamase.

value.value: PDC-65 is an ambler class C beta-lactamase found in Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
PDC-55 is an ambler class C beta-lactamase from Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
YajC interacts with the AcrAB-TolC efflux pump in a way that in uncharacterized but is shown to grant increased fitness in the presence of linezolid, rifampicin, and vancomycin.
mlaF from the mla system is a gene proposed to play a part in the transport of phospholipids to the outer membrane. Insertions in mlaF are shown to confer resistance to linezolid.
mlaD from the mla system is a gene proposed to play a part in the transport of phospholipids to the outer membrane. Insertions in mlaD are shown to confer resistance to linezolid.
cmlA9 is a Major Facilitator Superfamily efflux gene that is found in Salmonella enterica.
OmpA is a porin that confers resistance to beta-lactam antibiotics.
SatA is part of the Streptothricin acetyltransferase gene family. It confers resistance to nucleoside antibiotics.
